<DOC><DOCNO> AP881112-0133 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-12-88 2334EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-GulfCoastStorm     11-12 0136</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Gulf Coast Storm,0139</SECOND><HEAD>Girl Killed by Lightning; Tornado Strikes in Mississippi</HEAD><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   Lightning killed a 13-year-old girl in Louisiana and a tornadotouched down in Vicksburg, Miss., as thunderstorms, damaging windsand hail moved through the Gulf Coast region Saturday.   The National Weather Service said a cold front stretching acrossthe Mississippi Valley was responsible.   Ronda Weathersby died when lightning traveled down a tree in herback yard in Tallulah and struck her, said Chief Deputy John Bakerof the Madison Parish Sheriff's Department.   Winds were clocked at 60 mph in Jackson, Miss., and 52 mph inShreveport, La. High winds in other areas knocked out power linesand downed trees.   An inch of hail fell in Simmsboro, La.   The weather service forecast partly cloudy skies by Sunday withscattered showers.</TEXT></DOC>